565
00:39:52,012 --> 00:39:54,497
Why did you drop honorifics when I am this utterly without talent.

566
00:39:54,497 --> 00:39:55,820
Don't worry,

567
00:39:55,820 --> 00:39:57,658
you have your strengths too.

568
00:39:57,682 --> 00:39:59,107
It's alright,

569
00:39:59,107 --> 00:40:01,343
it's not even as if you're slapping my cheek, then humoring me.

570
00:40:03,721 --> 00:40:05,752
What's my strength?

571
00:40:07,200 --> 00:40:10,009
Your eyes.

572
00:40:10,972 --> 00:40:12,669
My eyes?

573
00:40:13,551 --> 00:40:15,015
Eyes that can tell

574
00:40:15,015 --> 00:40:18,912
whether the defendant is lying or telling the truth.

575
00:40:21,079 --> 00:40:23,402
No, but...

576
00:40:24,886 --> 00:40:27,049
Other than that, what other strengths do I have?

577
00:40:27,069 --> 00:40:29,433
Uh, other than that...

578
00:40:32,006 --> 00:40:33,508
there aren't any other.

579
00:40:33,508 --> 00:40:34,811
That doesn't make sense.

580
00:40:34,875 --> 00:40:37,483
I even went to the defendant's school for that case.

581
00:40:37,483 --> 00:40:39,199
That's because Lawyer Cha took you there.

582
00:40:39,199 --> 00:40:42,212
Even in court when the prosecutor made a rebuttal, I made a game saving tackle . . .

583
00:40:42,212 --> 00:40:44,948
You barely escaped only because I helped you.

584
00:40:44,964 --> 00:40:45,819
Also!

585
00:40:45,819 --> 00:40:47,230
What else is there?

586
00:40:47,281 --> 00:40:48,742
Also!

587
00:40:51,640 --> 00:40:53,144
Excuse me, can you please get me a glass of wine?

588
00:40:53,144 --> 00:40:54,380
I thought you said you don't drink!

589
00:40:54,380 --> 00:40:57,239
I said I won't, not that I can't!

590
00:41:09,404 --> 00:41:12,101
Why do I only have one strength?

591
00:41:12,433 --> 00:41:15,502
I asked why do I only have one strength?

592
00:41:17,931 --> 00:41:21,658
You should have said she had 10 or something. What is this now?

593
00:41:21,658 --> 00:41:24,674
Who knew she would whine this much?

594
00:41:24,674 --> 00:41:26,621
Let's go.

595
00:41:26,625 --> 00:41:28,605
Then, what about Lawyer Jang?

596
00:41:28,605 --> 00:41:31,213
Lawyer Cha can take care of that.

597
00:41:31,582 --> 00:41:33,639
Or you can.

598
00:41:33,639 --> 00:41:34,840
Yes?

599
00:41:34,840 --> 00:41:38,068
I'm sorry. Today's an ancestor's memorial, so I have to get going...

600
00:41:38,068 --> 00:41:41,021
I have to be there as the first son, so I'll be leaving first.

601
00:41:51,741 --> 00:41:55,431
Those eyes aren't mine.

602
00:41:56,801 --> 00:42:01,141
I don't have eyes that can see through the defendant.

603
00:42:01,141 --> 00:42:05,190
I don't see. I can't see.

604
00:42:14,183 --> 00:42:16,261
Where did everyone go?

605
00:42:16,881 --> 00:42:20,971
Lawyer Jang, where did everyone go?

606
00:42:20,971 --> 00:42:26,076
I don't know. They must have all left without telling me.

607
00:42:30,388 --> 00:42:33,482
Wow, her drunkenness is out there.

608
00:42:33,482 --> 00:42:36,422
I don't see the truth.

609
00:42:46,257 --> 00:42:48,017
Oh no!

610
00:42:48,502 --> 00:42:51,282
Now, I really can't see.

611
00:42:51,282 --> 00:42:55,223
What do I do? What should I do now?

612
00:42:56,355 --> 00:42:57,563
Here.

613
00:42:58,283 --> 00:42:59,528
Here.

614
00:43:00,257 --> 00:43:02,200
Can you see now?

615
00:43:05,009 --> 00:43:06,990
What should I do?

616
00:43:06,990 --> 00:43:09,330
My eyes must be crazy.

617
00:43:11,010 --> 00:43:14,144
Lawyer Cha has suddenly become a flower boy.

618
00:43:14,791 --> 00:43:17,599
Oh my eyes have gone bad.

619
00:43:17,599 --> 00:43:19,377
A flower boy.

620
00:43:26,558 --> 00:43:31,077
That's right. I'm not a good judge of people.

621
00:43:31,403 --> 00:43:34,789
So I need that piece of gum with me at all times.

622
00:43:34,789 --> 00:43:39,429
Lawyer Jang, we'll look for that piece of gum another time. Let's find your home first instead.

623
00:43:39,429 --> 00:43:41,453
Where is your house?

624
00:43:42,639 --> 00:43:47,079
If he's not around, I can't go into a courtroom.

625
00:43:47,079 --> 00:43:51,706
Why? Because my eyes have gone bad.

626
00:43:53,083 --> 00:43:55,196
I can't see again.

627
00:43:58,357 --> 00:44:00,996
Here.

628
00:44:00,996 --> 00:44:02,676
There you go.

629
00:44:02,676 --> 00:44:06,906
Excuse me, but where is your home?

630
00:44:06,906 --> 00:44:10,426
Geez, I'm going crazy.

631
00:44:19,657 --> 00:44:22,107
Why isn't she coming out?

632
00:44:23,197 --> 00:44:25,755
Why isn't she answering her phone?

633
00:44:31,868 --> 00:44:33,608
What is this?

634
00:44:38,394 --> 00:44:41,056
What's the matter? Are you sick?

635
00:44:43,522 --> 00:44:44,206
What a stench.

636
00:44:44,206 --> 00:44:46,906
Hey, you were the one who came into our office, right?

637
00:44:46,906 --> 00:44:47,910
Yes.

638
00:44:47,910 --> 00:44:50,419
But what are you doing here?

639
00:44:50,880 --> 00:44:53,259
I had something to say to Lawyer Jang.

640
00:44:53,259 --> 00:44:56,889
As you can clearly see, she not in a state to listen to you.

641
00:44:56,889 --> 00:44:58,689
<i>Where does she live exactly?</i>

642
00:44:58,689 --> 00:45:00,739
<i>I can't take her to my house either.</i>

643
00:45:00,739 --> 00:45:02,949
<i>Should I take her back to the office?</i>

644
00:45:02,949 --> 00:45:06,009
<i>It will be cold there at night.</i>

645
00:45:06,009 --> 00:45:08,919
I'll escort you to Lawyer Jang's house.

646
00:45:09,466 --> 00:45:10,889
You know where she lives?

647
00:45:10,889 --> 00:45:12,839
Yes, I've been there a few times.

648
00:45:12,839 --> 00:45:15,656
Hand her to me and catch us a taxi.

649
00:45:23,132 --> 00:45:26,696
Excuse me, but I'll take her by myself.

650
00:45:26,696 --> 00:45:30,456
You can take her by yourself? She's heavier than she appears.

651
00:45:30,456 --> 00:45:32,796
But for us to both take her home is a little excessive.

652
00:45:32,796 --> 00:45:34,509
Is that so?

653
00:45:36,542 --> 00:45:38,777
--Please take them safely.
--Yes.

654
00:45:40,176 --> 00:45:43,079
<i>Can I trust this rascal?</i>

655
00:45:44,825 --> 00:45:48,529
May I have one of your business cards, so that I can contact you after I get her home.

656
00:45:48,529 --> 00:45:50,083
Sure.

657
00:45:50,769 --> 00:45:53,529
If it's too difficult by yourself, contact me. I'll come right away.

658
00:45:53,529 --> 00:45:56,412
That's alright. I'll be fine by myself.

659
00:46:04,775 --> 00:46:06,189
Exactly how much

660
00:46:06,189 --> 00:46:10,007
did you eat at the party,

661
00:46:10,007 --> 00:46:12,891
that you're so heavy?

662
00:46:17,095 --> 00:46:18,505
Damn.

663
00:46:19,001 --> 00:46:21,412
It's still not fixed.

664
00:46:22,326 --> 00:46:25,132
After what happened, you should be cautious.

665
00:46:34,165 --> 00:46:44,284


666
00:46:51,020 --> 00:46:56,142
♪<i> What made you finally appear?</i>

667
00:46:56,142 --> 00:47:01,752
♪<i> Where were you? </i>

668
00:47:01,752 --> 00:47:09,488
♪<i>Even though it's a little late, still we've finally met.</i>

669
00:47:09,488 --> 00:47:11,492
This place is disgusting.

670
00:47:15,181 --> 00:47:17,639
Gum.

671
00:47:24,229 --> 00:47:27,978
Bring him here.

672
00:47:29,693 --> 00:47:32,559
I need him at court.

673
00:47:32,559 --> 00:47:34,689
What is she saying?

674
00:47:34,689 --> 00:47:37,598
I need Gum...

675
00:47:38,659 --> 00:47:42,836
He needs to be with me...

676
00:47:44,771 --> 00:47:48,325
My eyes are rotten.

677
00:48:27,010 --> 00:48:28,834
- Hello
<i>- Hey, you little brat!</i>

678
00:48:28,834 --> 00:48:30,774
Pick up the phone properly!

679
00:48:30,774 --> 00:48:33,064
<i>Do you want to see blood and death?</i>

680
00:48:33,064 --> 00:48:35,584
<i>Sober up, you wench!</i>

681
00:48:35,584 --> 00:48:38,584
Do you have to die in your mother's hands to get some sense?

682
00:48:38,584 --> 00:48:45,290
Mom, talk softly. My ear is going to explode.

683
00:48:46,624 --> 00:48:49,294
But what's wrong with your voice?

684
00:48:50,154 --> 00:48:52,264
Are you hurt anywhere?

685
00:48:54,163 --> 00:48:56,440
Yesterday, I had a dinner,

686
00:48:56,440 --> 00:48:58,414
and drank some alcohol. I must have lost it.

687
00:48:58,414 --> 00:49:00,634
But don't you hate alcohol?

688
00:49:00,634 --> 00:49:03,474
Why did you drink it then?

689
00:49:03,474 --> 00:49:05,494
Is there something wrong?

690
00:49:06,931 --> 00:49:12,859
Mom, should I go meet that bathhouse son from last time?

691
00:49:12,859 --> 00:49:16,459
Didn't you say you are forever married to the law?

692
00:49:16,459 --> 00:49:18,499
The law and I had a falling out.

693
00:49:18,499 --> 00:49:20,709
Why?

694
00:49:20,709 --> 00:49:24,199
I don't know. I guess the law didn't want to be married to me.

695
00:49:24,199 --> 00:49:31,041
How pathetic. You change your mind so easily.

696
00:49:32,200 --> 00:49:36,629
I know, right. Why am I like this?

697
00:49:43,715 --> 00:49:48,459
Hye Seong, do you even know how to do anything?

698
00:49:51,470 --> 00:49:53,319
You're coming now?

699
00:49:53,319 --> 00:49:55,609
Did you get home safely yesterday?

700
00:49:55,609 --> 00:49:57,719
Do your insides feel alright?

701
00:49:57,719 --> 00:49:58,919
Yes.

702
00:49:58,919 --> 00:50:00,959
How do I look?

703
00:50:00,959 --> 00:50:04,239
Do I still seem like a flower boy?

704
00:50:05,740 --> 00:50:07,430
Wake up!

705
00:50:07,430 --> 00:50:10,059
You seem to still be drunk!

706
00:50:20,789 --> 00:50:22,859
I must have been crazy.

707
00:50:22,859 --> 00:50:25,569
My eyes are really crazy.

708
00:50:26,439 --> 00:50:29,449
I'm sober now,

709
00:50:29,449 --> 00:50:32,674
but he still looks good even with those glasses.

710
00:50:45,762 --> 00:50:46,962
Good morning.

711
00:50:46,962 --> 00:50:48,562
Good morning.

712
00:50:58,262 --> 00:50:59,562
Why are you looking at me that way?

713
00:50:59,562 --> 00:51:02,362
Is something on my face?

714
00:51:02,362 --> 00:51:06,562
Yesterday, did anything happen with Lawyer Jang?

715
00:51:06,562 --> 00:51:08,262
Nothing really.

716
00:51:08,262 --> 00:51:11,849
Ah! The high school student we saw before. Did he say he was Park Soo Ha?

717
00:51:11,862 --> 00:51:13,862
That pal had come to get her.

718
00:51:13,862 --> 00:51:19,162
That kid seems to escort her here and back everyday. Maybe he's a bodyguard?

719
00:51:20,862 --> 00:51:22,062
Hey, Lawyer Cha.

720
00:51:22,062 --> 00:51:28,062
Have you asked Lawyer Jang whether she knows that person named Min Joon Gook or whatever?

721
00:51:35,350 --> 00:51:39,095
How do you, Lawyer Shin, know Min Joon Gook?

722
00:51:39,162 --> 00:51:42,662
I was told he was a cell mate of someone I know.

723
00:51:42,662 --> 00:51:45,362
Is he someone you know?

724
00:51:46,262 --> 00:51:47,862
Yes.

725
00:51:47,862 --> 00:51:50,662
That person, he was released a little while ago.

726
00:51:50,662 --> 00:51:53,962
I was told he had inquired after you.

727
00:51:54,662 --> 00:51:56,562
Released?

728
00:51:59,162 --> 00:52:01,762
When did he get released?

729
00:52:01,762 --> 00:52:04,862
It must have been about a month ago.

730
00:52:04,862 --> 00:52:08,362
He had some debt to repay to you?

731
00:52:19,062 --> 00:52:21,062
<i>I'll be there</i>

732
00:52:24,137 --> 00:52:28,133
Could it be that person sent this too?

733
00:52:44,562 --> 00:52:45,862
Sorry.

734
00:53:14,962 --> 00:53:17,062
What are you doing here?

735
00:53:18,162 --> 00:53:20,462
You didn't accept my calls, so I just came here.

736
00:53:20,462 --> 00:53:23,062
The incident happened so long ago, and you still haven't fixed your lock?

737
00:53:23,062 --> 00:53:24,515
Go.

738
00:53:24,515 --> 00:53:26,162
I'll take care of it.

739
00:53:26,162 --> 00:53:29,062
It's alright. I'm doing this in thanks for saving Seong Bin.

740
00:53:29,062 --> 00:53:31,762
I told you go!

741
00:53:35,520 --> 00:53:37,260
What's up? Is something wrong?

742
00:53:37,260 --> 00:53:38,758
Get lost! Go!

743
00:53:38,762 --> 00:53:41,062
Don't come here again!

744
00:53:44,662 --> 00:53:47,262
<i>I don't know if this rascal is with Min Joon Gook or not.</i>

745
00:54:03,562 --> 00:54:04,762
Hello?

746
00:54:04,772 --> 00:54:06,431
It's me.

747
00:54:06,462 --> 00:54:08,662
You remember my voice, right?

748
00:54:09,662 --> 00:54:12,862
Ah, yes. You're Min Joon Gook, right?

749
00:54:12,862 --> 00:54:14,562
How did you know my number?

750
00:54:14,562 --> 00:54:17,862
I went to your school yesterday,

751
00:54:17,862 --> 00:54:20,762
Park Soo Ha.

752
00:54:20,762 --> 00:54:23,565
You didn't tell me your name, so I didn't recognize you.

753
00:54:23,565 --> 00:54:26,962
I last saw you at court, ten years ago?

754
00:54:26,978 --> 00:54:30,603
You... Where are you right now?

755
00:54:49,762 --> 00:54:53,662
I didn't know what you liked, so I got this.

756
00:54:53,662 --> 00:54:55,062
Eat.

757
00:54:56,262 --> 00:54:59,262
<i>You came, little one.</i>

758
00:54:59,262 --> 00:55:01,562
What are you thinking up?

759
00:55:02,262 --> 00:55:05,862
<i>You grew a lot, little one.</i>

760
00:55:05,862 --> 00:55:11,562
<i>Your ability to read my thoughts that you had 10 years ago doesn't seemed to have changed</i>

761
00:55:11,562 --> 00:55:15,362
Speak up, and don't think them.

762
00:55:15,362 --> 00:55:17,145
<i>What are you worried about?</i>

763
00:55:17,162 --> 00:55:20,962
<i>Why, you think I'm going to cause some trouble?</i>

764
00:55:21,862 --> 00:55:27,262
The cellphone is your doing, isn't it? You sent it.

765
00:55:31,362 --> 00:55:36,962
<i>Are you getting scared from just that? When I haven't even started...</i>

766
00:55:36,980 --> 00:55:39,437
What are you thinking.

767
00:55:39,462 --> 00:55:41,387
<i>Don't worry. </i>

768
00:55:41,387 --> 00:55:44,662
<i>I don't have any hard feelings towards you.</i>

769
00:55:44,678 --> 00:55:49,137
<i>10 years ago the target wasn't you, but your father.</i>

770
00:55:49,137 --> 00:55:53,754
<i>This time too... it isn't you, but someone else.</i>

771
00:55:57,162 --> 00:56:01,362
If it's not me, who is it?

772
00:56:01,362 --> 00:56:07,162
<i>She became a lawyer, I've heard. That girl.</i>

773
00:56:14,262 --> 00:56:16,562
Let go of me!

774
00:56:21,595 --> 00:56:24,723
Ahh! Save me!

775
00:56:59,962 --> 00:57:01,662
Hello?

776
00:57:03,962 --> 00:57:05,562
At the police station?

777
00:57:08,662 --> 00:57:10,762
Ms. Jang Hye Seong! Hello.

778
00:57:10,862 --> 00:57:11,862
What happened?

779
00:57:11,862 --> 00:57:17,362
You know Park Soo Ha, the kid who was with you at the cell phone incident, right?

780
00:57:17,380 --> 00:57:18,846
Yes.

781
00:57:18,862 --> 00:57:22,062
Right now, that student beat up someone and is here.

782
00:57:22,062 --> 00:57:26,462
A guardian has to sign him out, but he doesn't have parents and we can't contact his teacher.

783
00:57:26,462 --> 00:57:30,062
So for now, I've called Lawyer Jang over.

784
00:57:30,062 --> 00:57:31,432
What about the victim?

785
00:57:31,432 --> 00:57:34,562
He left saying he doesn't want to charge for anything.

786
00:57:34,562 --> 00:57:39,262
He just got released, so I guess he doesn't want to get involved in anything.

787
00:57:40,137 --> 00:57:41,481
Released?

788
00:57:41,481 --> 00:57:45,935
Yes. But the CCTV caught Park Soo Ha beating him up.

789
00:57:45,962 --> 00:57:50,162
I can't give him bail unless someone can be liable for him.

790
00:57:52,062 --> 00:57:53,762
What was the victim's name?

791
00:57:53,775 --> 00:57:59,683
Yes, it's Min Joon Gook. He got released last month.

792
00:57:59,729 --> 00:58:01,387
What?

793
00:58:01,428 --> 00:58:04,562
Do you know this person?

794
00:58:06,562 --> 00:58:10,162
May I see the CCTV?

795
00:58:10,162 --> 00:58:12,962
Let's see...

796
00:58:12,962 --> 00:58:14,964
Did Soo Ha say why he hit him?

797
00:58:14,964 --> 00:58:20,262
I don't know. From what witnesses say, it was just a fit of rage.

798
00:58:20,962 --> 00:58:22,862
There has to be a reason though.

799
00:58:22,928 --> 00:58:24,463
Yeah, but there isn't any!

800
00:58:24,463 --> 00:58:26,144
Min Joon Gook didn't say a word,

801
00:58:26,144 --> 00:58:30,268
but then Park Soo Ha punched him!

802
00:58:30,362 --> 00:58:34,362
I was there too. Min Joon Gook really didn't say anything.

803
00:58:34,362 --> 00:58:37,762
Soo Ha was the only one talking.

804
00:58:39,962 --> 00:58:41,862
Ah! Here it is! I found it!

805
00:58:41,867 --> 00:58:43,062
This here.

806
00:58:49,562 --> 00:58:51,263
What is Soo Ha saying?

807
00:58:51,263 --> 00:58:53,662
What did he say?

808
00:58:53,726 --> 00:58:58,012
Ah. He kept telling Min Joon Gook to speak up.

809
00:58:58,062 --> 00:59:01,462
Not to think, but speak.

810
00:59:04,171 --> 00:59:05,387
Say it, bastard!

811
00:59:05,387 --> 00:59:08,689
Say what you're thinking!

812
00:59:09,462 --> 00:59:11,062
<i>I don't want to.</i>

813
00:59:11,062 --> 00:59:13,262
What are you doing? Let go and talk it out.

814
00:59:16,550 --> 00:59:19,357
If that person wasn't there I would've died 10 years ago.

815
00:59:19,362 --> 00:59:23,862
That's why think of my life as hers!

816
00:59:23,862 --> 00:59:26,062
I'm going to protect her.

817
00:59:29,462 --> 00:59:32,678
Get lost! I'm letting my life hang on the line to protect her.

818
00:59:32,762 --> 00:59:35,562
Don't you dare do anything, because I'll kill you.

819
00:59:37,762 --> 00:59:40,462
I'll kill you with my own hands.

820
00:59:40,462 --> 00:59:44,662
If he bothers that woman, he announced he'd kill him.

821
00:59:44,685 --> 00:59:46,641
I thought I was going to poop in my pants trying to hold him off.

822
00:59:46,662 --> 00:59:48,662
He's totally crazy.

823
00:59:50,262 --> 00:59:52,906
This punk, he even brought a hammer with him!

824
00:59:52,906 --> 00:59:56,762
If he'd used this, this would've been a much bigger situation.

825
01:00:01,762 --> 01:00:02,962
<i>Listen to me carefully.</i>

826
01:00:02,978 --> 01:00:06,346
<i>If she wasn't there 10 years ago, I would've been killed by you.</i>

827
01:00:11,662 --> 01:00:15,662
<i>I... I...</i>

828
01:00:17,762 --> 01:00:19,845
<i>will... protect you...</i>

829
01:00:19,862 --> 01:00:24,862
<i>I wouldn't have lived if it weren't for her, so I'm going to protect her even if it kills me.</i>

830
01:00:28,962 --> 01:00:31,962
<i>I'll risk my life to protect her.</i>

831
01:00:32,462 --> 01:00:34,963
<i>I... </i>

832
01:00:35,803 --> 01:00:38,862
<i>will... protect you...</i>

833
01:00:40,262 --> 01:00:42,062
<i>What is this...</i>

834
01:00:42,101 --> 01:00:44,554
<i>You know how to talk.</i>

835
01:00:48,642 --> 01:00:50,727
<i>Kid.</i>

836
01:00:50,762 --> 01:00:52,862
<i>What is your name?</i>

837
01:00:53,962 --> 01:00:56,095
<i>Soo Ha...</i>

838
01:00:57,162 --> 01:01:00,062
<i>Park Soo Ha.</i>

839
01:01:12,385 --> 01:01:15,431
I will be liable for him.

840
01:01:15,462 --> 01:01:16,362
Where's Soo Ha?

841
01:01:16,362 --> 01:01:17,362
<i>Police</i>

842
01:01:19,451 --> 01:01:22,055
You let Min Joon Gook go!

843
01:01:22,062 --> 01:01:24,362
Did you get his address? What about his phone number?

844
01:01:24,362 --> 01:01:27,862
Hey, you seem to be misunderstanding something.

845
01:01:27,894 --> 01:01:30,556
You were the one hitting. Min Joon Gook was the one getting hit.

846
01:01:30,562 --> 01:01:34,862
You're the culprit. He's the victim. You got that?

847
01:01:35,262 --> 01:01:38,462
Do know what he said? He's going to take revenge.

848
01:01:38,462 --> 01:01:41,762
He's going to find the one who testified against him and kill her.

849
01:01:41,762 --> 01:01:44,262
I believed you and asked all the witnesses at the restaurant.

850
01:01:44,262 --> 01:01:46,162
There were no such words.

851
01:01:46,162 --> 01:01:49,662
Min Joon Gook volunteers at

852
01:01:49,662 --> 01:01:53,162
more than 6 places, such as soup kitchens and animal shelters.

853
01:01:53,239 --> 01:01:57,937
He changed for the better. Yet you're accusing him without any evidence.

854
01:01:58,562 --> 01:02:02,262
You should, at least, bring some evidence.

855
01:02:08,198 --> 01:02:09,523
There's evidence.

856
01:02:09,523 --> 01:02:12,024
What? What evidence?

857
01:02:13,962 --> 01:02:16,162
I heard it. I can hear minds...

858
01:02:16,162 --> 01:02:18,162
Stop it.

859
01:02:21,362 --> 01:02:23,662
<i>Don't say anything that's useless.</i>

860
01:02:24,862 --> 01:02:30,562
<i>You'll just get treated like you did 10 years ago in court.</i>

861
01:02:31,662 --> 01:02:34,262
<i>Park Soo Ha.</i>

862
01:02:35,262 --> 01:02:38,862
<i>I remember your name now.</i>

863
01:02:41,662 --> 01:02:55,162
